    <titleInfo>
        <title>Rising from the Ashes: The Chimney Tops 2 Wildfires in Memory and Art</title>
    </titleInfo>
    <abstract>The Chimney Tops 2 wildfires, one of the largest natural disasters in Tennessee history, 
        began on November 23, 2016 in the Great Smoky Mountains National Park and caused fourteen deaths, 
        injuries to more than 200 individuals, and the evacuation of thousands of people. The University of 
        Tennessee Libraries, with support from the city of Gatlinburg and partnership from the Anna Porter Public Library, 
        captured the stories of those affected by the wildfires through recording oral histories. This collection features art created by 
        illustrators Paige Braddock, Marshall Ramsey, and Danny Wilson in response to these interviews.</abstract>
